I'm pissed about Biden things this morning, so bear with me.

First of all, that quote from Angelo yesterday afternoon is out of context. Yes, he was talking to rich people and asking them for money, and part of that was assuring them that he wouldn't hike taxes **too** much, but that hardly calls for the bumper sticker response from the media and the left.  Here is the full quote:

>By the way, you know, remember I got in trouble with some of the people on my team, on the Democratic side, because I said, ‘You know what I’ve found is rich people are just as patriotic as poor people.’ Not a joke. I mean, we may not want to demonize anybody who has made money. The truth of the matter is, you all, you all know, you all know in your gut what has to be done. We can disagree in the margins but the truth of the matter is it’s all within our wheelhouse and nobody has to be punished. No one’s standard of living will change, nothing would fundamentally change. Because when we have income inequality as large as we have in the United States today, it brews and ferments political discord and basic revolution. Not a joke. Not a joke. I’m not [inaudible] revolution. But not a joke. It allows demagogues to step in and say the reason where we are is because of the other, the other. You’re not the other. I need you very badly. I hope if I win this nomination, I won’t let you down.

If you read the whole thing, basically what he was saying is that he would raise taxes on the rich, but that they'd be fine. Also known as how literally everyone on Earth feels on this issue.
Second, "Boy"? Really, Biden? You fucking out of touch idiot.

But again, what pisses me off about that one is that people are mad at him for compromising with segregationists in a time when that was absolutely necessary and his job, not for not understanding that a racist calling him "son" instead of "boy" was due to his skin color, and is not at all something to joke about.
Just goes to show that you can't be 75 and understand how the world works now.
That's all, thanks for reading if you did.  Just really needed to get that off my chest this morning.
No, what pisses me off is he feels the need to bring it up to try and contextualize his ability to TCB.

It's also fundamentally naive. Doing a thing with your own party members 300 years ago might not apply do doing a thing with the opposition party today, and he seems to not get there isn't a 1:1 translation there
Sigh. Compromise isn't evil, racism is. The fact that we're upset about the former and not the latter just goes to show how much of an effect Trump has had on our national discourse.

I think you're reading what you want to into the arguments. Nobody is saying compromise is evil, because Biden isn't arguing that you can work with people if necessary no matter how shitty they are. He's arguing that he can get things done with shitty people.
The difference is the shitty people back then were willing to compromise, and he assumes that they'll do the same here, because of his Bidenness

The problem is Biden fundamentally misunderstands the situation. He thinks working with racist Democrats back in the day when there were deals to be made that benefited them and the political body was a different thing means he can work with racist Republicans today in a much different world.
Whether or not you think that we live in a post-compromise world or not means nothing when the actual discussion should be "a 75 year old man thinks it's okay to make jokes about slave terms".
There's a ton wrong with what Biden said. That's one of them, but it's not the only one.
And I get what your're saying that we shouldn't minimize him not getting that slave term jokes are okay. That's a problem and it makes things worse.

But him not understanding the world has changed and he's not gonna magically return us to an era of bipartisanship via being Joe Biden is also a problem that makes things worse, and minimizing THAT is an issue too
It really, really isn't.
If you don't think a potential nominee not understanding the current state of partisanship isn't a problem, then okay. We'll disagree there.
You're completely right about how the the joke about slave terms thing is a problem though. I'm with you there all the way.
